.TH GIT\-ISSUE\-SHOW 1 "2026-02-07" "git-issue 1.0.0" "Git Issue Manual"
.SH NAME
git\-issue\-show \- show issue details and comments
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git issue show
.I <issue-id>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Display the full details of an issue including its title, author,
creation date, metadata (labels, assignee, priority, milestone),
description body, and all subsequent updates (comments and state
changes) in chronological order.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I <issue-id>
Full UUID or abbreviated prefix (minimum 4 characters).
If the prefix is ambiguous, all matching issues are listed and
the command exits with an error.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show usage information.
.SH EXAMPLES
Show an issue by short ID:
.RS
.nf
$ git issue show a1b2c3d
.fi
.RE
.PP
Show an issue by full UUID:
.RS
.nf
$ git issue show a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git\-issue (1),
.BR git\-issue\-ls (1),
.BR git\-issue\-comment (1)
